# Example flow — starting point, copy to .thenn/ and make it your own
# Self-contained: uses inline prompts, no external commands required
# Artifacts produced: .thenn-state/{context,findings-*,actions}.md
#
# Demonstrates the coordinator type: a step that runs in the
# orchestrator's main conversation (not as a subagent) so it can fan
# out to multiple subagents in parallel. type: agent cannot do this —
# a subagent cannot spawn further subagents. Only the runner can,
# which is what type: coordinator turns you into.

name: example-coordinator
description: Coordinator fan-out — gather context, three parallel investigations, synthesize, review
input: "What do you want to build or change?"

steps:
  - id: gather-context
    type: agent
    input: true
    prompt: "Read README.md and CLAUDE.md (if present). Write a short context brief — what the project is, who uses it, the stack, and any constraints — to .thenn-state/context.md."

  - id: parallel-investigate
    type: coordinator        # runner does the work, can spawn subagents
    input: false
    prompt: |
      Read .thenn-state/context.md. You are the thenn-runner orchestrator
      acting as a context-light coordinator — fan out to three parallel
      investigations using the Agent tool:
      1. Performance — hot paths, slow queries, unnecessary work
      2. Security — unsafe input handling, secrets, auth gaps
      3. Maintainability — code smells, dead code, missing tests

      For each angle, spawn a general-purpose subagent with a clear, scoped
      brief. Each subagent writes findings to .thenn-state/findings-<angle>.md.
      Do not redo the investigation yourself — your job is to coordinate.

      Return a one-line summary per angle when done. The thenn-runner will
      then move to the next step.

  - id: synthesize
    type: agent
    input: false
    prompt: "Read .thenn-state/findings-{performance,security,maintainability}.md. Synthesize into a prioritized action list at .thenn-state/actions.md (top 5-10 items, each with file:line references where possible)."

  - id: review
    type: human
    message: "Review .thenn-state/actions.md. Mark items to act on, then press Continue"
